  ('Carbon dioxide (CO₂) is non-polar despite having polar C=O bonds because ___.',['carbon has no electronegativity','the bonds are ionic','it has only two bonds','the linear geometry means the two bond dipoles point in opposite directions and exactly cancel, giving CO₂ a net dipole of zero'],3),
