  ('Canadian literature\'s sense of "garrison mentality" (Northrop Frye\'s concept) refers to ___.',['an obsession with military history','only Quebec literature','only Indigenous literature','a recurring theme of small communities — physical and psychological — fighting to maintain identity and safety against a threatening, overwhelming landscape or outside force'],3),
